  "body": "Currently, we've configured our node to send prometheus metrics to Datadog. Due to an absence of a TYPE(i.e. `gauge`) for these metrics, these untyped metrics are ignored by default and it requires a manual cast of metrics in the `Datadog config` file to get the metric successfully sent to Datadog. Can the team specify the type for these prometheus metrics in the code? \r\n\r\n```\r\ninstances:\r\n  - prometheus_url: http://localhost:26660/debug/metrics/prometheus\r\n    namespace: \"erigon\"\r\n    type_overrides:\r\n      table_log_branch: gauge\r\n      sync: gauge\r\n```\r\n      \r\n      ",
